elements.desc: r06_TypeOfCompressorControl (RW)(NL)reg:207(NL)(NL)Description:(NL)Type of compressor control(NL)(NL)Value Meanings:(NL)0=proportional on inlet(NL)1=proportional on inlet + dead zone(NL)2=proportional on outlet(NL)3=proportional on outlet + dead zone(NL)4=time on outlet with dead zone(NL)Type of compressor control (r06)(NL)This parameter is used to set the logic for maintaining the set point: (NL)0=proportional on inlet,(NL)1=proportional on inlet + dead zone,(NL)2=proportional on outlet,(NL)3=proportional on outlet + dead zone,(NL)4=time on outlet with dead zone(NL)(NL)DEAD ZONE(NL)The dead zone essentially shifts the proportional band from the set point(NL)by the value set for the parameter r07. This parameter is valid in all(NL)configurations if enabled (for r07≠0: dead zone set and enabled).(NL)In chiller (cooling) mode, the dead zone moves the cooling proportional band above the set point(NL)by the value r07.(NL)Outlet temperature control by time r06 = 4 (only chiller)(NL)This type of control is based on the need to maintain the outlet(NL)temperature as constant as possible, despite the load being variable or(NL)the reduced inertia of the system. The logic has the aim of keeping the(NL)temperature inside the dead zone. If outside the zone, the compressors(NL)will be activated with the logic described below, so as to return inside(NL)the dead zone, neither too quickly (using an integral or derivative),(NL)nor too slowly, with fixed time logic. There are two logical times(NL)involved: the activation time and deactivation time.(NL)range:  - , default: 0(NL)value: 0
elements.name: r06_TypeOfCompressorControl
